==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|malliable|lang=enm}}, borrowed from {{etyl|LL.|en}} {{term/t|la|malleābilis}}, derived from {{term/t|la|malleāre||to hammer}}, from {{term|malleus||hammer|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*mal-ni-||crushing}}, an extended variant of {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*melH₂-||crush, grind}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈmæliəbəl/}}
* {{audio|en-us-malleable.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{hyphenation|mal|le|a|ble}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Able to be [[hammer]]ed into [[thin]] [[sheet]]s; capable of being [[extend]]ed or [[shape]]d by [[beat]]ing with a [[hammer]], or by the pressure of [[roller]]s.
# (''metaphorical'') [[flexible|Flexible]], [[liable]] to [[change]].
#: ''My opinion on the subject is '''malleable'''.''
# {{context|cryptography|of an algorithm|lang=en}} in which an adversary can alter a [[ciphertext]] such that it [[decrypts]] to a related [[plaintext]]

